Day	Topic	Tasks & Practice
1	Install Linux	Install Ubuntu (dual-boot/VirtualBox/WSL). Run uname -a.
2	Basic Commands	ls, cd, mkdir, touch, rm. Create /home/$USER/test.
3	File Permissions	chmod 644 file.txt, chown, chgrp. Make a script executable.
4	Text Editors	Edit files with nano & vim. Save and exit (:wq).
5	Process Management	ps aux, kill -9 PID, top, htop. Kill a running sleep process.
6	User Management	sudo adduser devops, passwd, usermod.
7	Networking Basics	ifconfig, ping, netstat -tuln, ssh.
8	Package Management	apt update, apt install nginx, systemctl start nginx.
9	Environment Variables	echo $PATH, export VAR="Hello", env.
10	Basic Shell Scripting	#!/bin/bash, echo "Hello World", make it executable.
11	Variables & Loops	for i in {1..5}; do echo $i; done.
12	If-Else Conditions	Check if a file exists, compare numbers.
13	Functions in Bash	Write a function to greet a user.
14	Automate a Backup	Backup /home to /backup with tar.
15	Cron Jobs	Schedule a script to run every day at 5 PM.
16	AWK & SED Basics	awk '{print $1}' file.txt, sed 's/old/new/g'.
17	Log Analysis	Use grep to find errors in /var/log/syslog.
18	Debugging Scripts	set -x, bash -x script.sh.
19	Mini-Project 1	Write a script to monitor disk space & alert if >90%.
20	Mini-Project 2	Automate user creation with a script.
21	Review & Practice	Redo all exercises, fix mistakes.
ðŸ“Œ Weeks 4-6: AWS & Cloud Basics (Days 22-42)
Day	Topic	Tasks & Practice
22	AWS Free Tier Setup	Enable MFA, set billing alerts.
23	EC2 Basics	Launch an Ubuntu instance, SSH into it.
24	EC2 Security Groups	Allow HTTP/HTTPS/SSH traffic.
25	S3 Basics	Create a bucket, upload a file, set permissions.
26	IAM Users & Roles	Create a user with S3 read-only access.
27	Route 53 Basics	Register a domain (optional), create a hosted zone.
28	CloudWatch Logs	Monitor EC2 CPU usage, set an alarm.
29	AWS CLI Setup	Install & configure (aws configure).
30	EBS Volumes	Attach a volume to EC2, format & mount it.
31	Load Balancers	Create an ALB, route traffic to 2 EC2 instances.
32	Auto Scaling	Configure an Auto Scaling group.
33	RDS Basics	Launch a MySQL DB, connect via MySQL client.
34	Lambda Basics	Create a Python Lambda function.
35	CloudFormation	Deploy an EC2 instance using a YAML template.
36	VPC & Subnets	Create a custom VPC with public/private subnets.
37	NAT Gateway	Allow private instances to access the internet.
38	AWS Cost Explorer	Analyze your AWS spending.
39	AWS Backup	Schedule an EBS snapshot backup.
40	AWS CLI Scripting	Automate EC2 instance start/stop.
41	Mini-Project 3	Host a static website on S3 + CloudFront.
42	Review & Practice	Recreate all AWS services from scratch.
ðŸ“Œ Weeks 7-9: Git, GitHub & CI/CD (Days 43-63)
Day	Topic	Tasks & Practice
43	Install Git	git --version, git config --global user.name.
44	Git Basics	git init, git add, git commit -m "message".
45	Git Log & Diff	git log --oneline, git diff.
46	Branching	git checkout -b feature, git merge.
47	GitHub Account	Push a local repo to GitHub.
48	Fork & PR	Fork a repo, make changes, submit a PR.
49	Git Stash	git stash, git stash pop.
50	Git Reset/Revert	Undo commits (git reset --hard HEAD~1).
51	Git Hooks	Create a pre-commit hook to block bad commits.
52	GitHub Actions	Run a simple workflow on push.
53	Jenkins Setup	Install Jenkins, run a "Hello World" job.
54	Docker Basics	docker run hello-world, docker ps -a.
55	Dockerfile	Build a custom Nginx image.
56	Docker Compose	Run a multi-container app (WordPress + MySQL).
57	Kubernetes Basics	minikube start, kubectl get pods.
58	Helm Basics	Install a chart (e.g., helm install nginx).
59	Terraform Basics	Deploy an EC2 instance using Terraform.
60	Ansible Basics	Write a playbook to install Nginx.
61	CI/CD Pipeline	Build a GitHub Actions pipeline for a Python app.
62	Mini-Project 4	Automate deployment of a web app (Docker + GitHub Actions).
63	Review & Practice	Break & fix a CI/CD pipeline.
ðŸ“Œ Weeks 10-12: Advanced DevOps (Days 64-90)
Day	Topic	Tasks & Practice
64-70	Monitoring (Prometheus + Grafana)	Set up alerts for CPU/RAM usage.
71-77	Infrastructure as Code (Terraform)	Deploy a full VPC + EC2 + RDS setup.
78-84	Kubernetes (EKS)	Deploy a microservice app on EKS.
85-90	Final Project	Build a full DevOps pipeline:
- CI/CD (GitHub Actions/Jenkins)
- IaC (Terraform)
- Kubernetes (EKS)
- Monitoring (Prometheus/Grafana)
